article.headline: Delaware St. 24, Bethune-Cookman 10
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Shaheer McBride caught five passes for 111 yards and two touchdowns, leading Delaware State to a 24-10 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Thursday night. Vashon Winton was 8 of 15 for 177 yards and also scored a touchdown rushing for the Hornets (4-1, 3-0), who trailed 10-7 midway through the third quarter before scoring the final 17 points. Peter Gaertner kicked a 28-yard field goal to tie it, and Winton hit McBride on a 37-yard touchdown pass with 12 seconds left in the third quarter. His 24-yard touchdown pass to McBride with 5:57 left put it away. Jimmie Russell was 7 of 16 for 102 yards with an interception, and carried 27 times for 175 yards for Bethune-Cookman (2-4, 1-4). He scored the team's only touchdown on a 3-yard run midway through the first quarter. It was Delaware State's first home game since a shooting on campus last month that injured two students.
